            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34982",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you help me by expanding the test case code? How is $router defined?\n\nthanks,\n-L",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-29T14:39:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-29T14:39:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34990",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=vladar",
                        "name": "vladar",
                        "displayName": "Vladimir Razuvaev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Here is a full test case code:\n\n[code]\n$front = Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance();\n\/\/ default ZF router:\n$router  = $front->getRouter();\n$router->removeDefaultRoutes();\n\n$route = new Zend_Controller_Router_Route('api');\n$router->addRoute(\"api\", $route->chain(new Zend_Rest_Route($front)));\n[\/code]\n\nWhen trying to navigate to \/api\/controller\/id exception is thrown:\nZend\\Controller\\Router\\Rewrite.php, line 341: Current route is not defined\n\nCurrently, I have subclassed Zend_Rest_Route with following code to make it work in chains:\n\n[code]\nclass RestRoute extends Zend_Rest_Route\n{\n    public function match($request, $partial = false)\n    {\n        $result = parent::match($request);\n        if($partial && $result) {\n            $this->setMatchedPath($request->getPathInfo());\n        }\n        return $result;\n    }\n}\n\n[\/code]\n\nThis is trivially copy-paste from Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Module",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=vladar",
                        "name": "vladar",
                        "displayName": "Vladimir Razuvaev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-29T23:04:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-29T23:04:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35151",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Added partial logic to Zend_Rest_Route::match to support using Zend_Rest_Route in route chains.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
